oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Thirty-First Annual Conference (1998). A Message From The President
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: There are a couple of characteristics that are frequently attributed to veterinarians; that we tend to be excellent problem solvers, and we are quite versatile. Some have suggested that the selection process for veterinary school, as well as the nature of the profession itself, tends to naturally select for those personal attributes. But maybe, instead, it is the prolific amount of advice, constructive criticism, insightful questions, and great respect we receive from our clients beginning very early in our careers.
